race.comment: REAL ALLIANCE (6) has been finishing off in stronger races and looks well placed in a country Open. Wasn't too far away at Flemington last time and expect her to settle back and come hard. FATHER'S DAY (2) has his third start for the yard and the former Sydney galloper should be ready to show more. Proven third-up and has Randwick form at 88 level that reads well. FLYING BASIL (3) will also be fitter and has jumped out well since last seen. Is a four-time winner over this journey and is drawn favourably. Expecting sharp improvement. SIRIUS BLACK (5) was a tough winner fresh but less effective last time. Best efforts measure up, so worth keeping safe.
